Learn git Part -1 :

1) git init  = make git file localy
2) git add [filename] || -A   = add files to git file
3) git status   = checking status whether file is added or not in git.
4) git commit -m "msg"  = make snapshot for new changes
5) git remote add origin repoName  = add to github repository
6) git push origin master = update to github repository
7) git clone repoName  = clone any github to local
8) git pull origin origin master  = update any github to local